The '''Imperial Military Code''' supervised the running of the [[Imperial Military/Legends|Imperial Military]] and its soldiers.

Section 12-C defined capital offenses, which included incitement to mutiny, participation in mutiny, concealing mutineers or evidence of mutiny or planned mutiny and concealing saboteurs or evidence of sabotage or planned sabotage.

